node.text: Same rally test stage, but two VERY different vehicles. Directly compare these onboard videos of an AWD Subaru STI rally car -VS- a RWD Trophy Truck. The truck has 3x the power but more than 2x the weight. This is my kind of science! #WhoopocalypseNow #SubaruSTI #TrophyTruck

node.title: AWD Subaru STI rally car -VS- a RWD Trophy Truck

node.text: The MTB trails at Woodward Park City are really damn fun right now! Here’s a full top-to-bottom clip of one of my favorite trails, on my new’ish Specialized Enduro. This trail doesn’t have the biggest jumps of the park on it, but I really love it. #SpecializedEnduro #woodwardparkcity @woodwardparkcity

node.title: Downhill POV run at Woodward Park City

node.text: More video action from my first day in a Trophy Truck (two of them actually - old and new @GeiserBros trucks) - and first time ripping at 100+ MPH through big whoops! I learned a lot pretty quickly, but of course still have plenty more to figure out before I’ll be ready to race with @JaxRedline in the Baja 1000 later this year. Holy crap, that was FUN.

node.title: First day in a Trophy Truck!

node.text: Such a rad time with an awesome group of peoples. The @GridExperience definitely sets the bar (and sets it pretty high) for me when it comes to indoor karting. Combine that with a this crew of friends and fam: Jeremy McGrath, Sage Kotsenburg, Zak Hale, Davey Coombs (founder of Racer X), Zac Mertens (of Hoonigan Racing), etc. - plus Jett and Hunter Lawrence were two of the top three fastest of the night (same positions as they finished in the 250 Main of the Supercross race this past weekend!). Jeremy’s daughter (Rhowan) and my daughter (Lia) both had two of the top lap five times also (yep, we’re proud Dads!). Good times!

node.title: Rad time karting at The Grid Experience with friends and fam.

node.text: The @GridExperience’s indoor kart track is really amazing. It’s a half mile long, 3-level, has two banked corners, a drop - and the electric karts have a boost button! This is the most fun indoor karting track I have EVER driven. Here’s a helmet cam clip of one of my fastest laps of the night racing with Jeremy McGrath, Jett Lawrence, Sage Kotsenburg, etc. Enjoy!

node.title: Indoor Karting at The Grid Experience

node.text: Two incredible rally cars tested back-to-back in the name of science - in this week’s episode on my YouTube channel. If you want to learn more about these two cars, and the differences between them when ripping around on gravel, click the link (in my bio) to watch the full episode.

node.text: Onboard action from today on Stage 2: “Plug Mill” (Reverse), in the @OlympusRally. 6.76 miles of fast gravel roads weaving through sections of dense, almost black forest and patches of completely clear cut land. We’re still getting a feel for how this car reacts in these soupy and wet conditions, and struggling a bit to find the speed I want. Working on it though! #dirtfisholympusrally

node.title: ARA DirtFish Olympus Rally - SS2 Onboard

node.text: This weekend will be my first competitive drive in a Subaru since 2009. With only one proper day of testing before @AlexGelsomino and I show up this weekend to the @OlympusRally (3rd round of the @ARA_Rally Championship) it will be interesting to see how quickly I can get fully comfortable in it and run at full tilt. But so far, the car looks (livery by @ItsALiving) and feels (built and prepped by Vermont SportsCar) great! Check out this week's episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) for the livery reveal, and to hear about all our plans for a wild year! #gravelslayingaction

node.title: Back In A Subaru - Just Gravel Test Acton

node.text: Here’s another AINT CARE moment from the vault: @AlexGelsomino and I lost our front right side wheel midway through Stage 3 (of Oregon Trail Rally in 2013) due to a freak mechanical failure. We kept the hammer down and finished that stage, and then continued on to run another full stage on just 3 wheels, rather than settling for a DNF. We finished the race 2nd overall - all because we were able to drive through this #AINTCARE situation!

node.title: JUST AIN’T CARE from Oregon Trail Rally 2013

node.text: AIN’T CARE, rally cross example: after qualifying first, winning each of the heats, and leading the first 5 laps of the Final in the 2012 GRC race in Las Vegas, the ECU/control panel in my race car caught fire. I continued the race for as long as I could, but the fumes from the fire were starting to burn my lungs. I led and raced for as long as I could but eventually had to stop. I truly tried to AIN’T CARE as long as I could, but wasn’t willing to die for the win. 🤷‍♂️ #AINTCARE #pressonregardless

node.title: AIN’T CARE - GRC Las Vegas - FIRE

node.text: Lots of rain prior to The Rally in the 100 Acre Wood this year made for some very wet and rough stretches of the race stages. This video from Stage 12 is a sample of that at this year’s race in Salem, Missouri. @AlexGelsomino and I were fastest on this stage during the race, helping us secure 2nd place overall. Click the link to see the full on-board video from the entire 10.84 mile stage. #100AW

node.title: Raw Onboard Rally Footage - 100 Acre Wood

node.text: V8 noises, big jumps, 100mph through the whoops… this Trophy Truck is really starting to grow on me. Here’s a bit of video from my co-driver @alexgelsomino and I testing and prepping for next week’s “Vegas to Reno” race. #WhoopocalypseNow #TrophyTruck

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ken Block on August 07, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: This beast absolutely rips!! @alexgelsomino and I spent the last two days smashing whoops, catching air, and learning the intricacies of this 1100 hp truck - all in the 120 degree heat of Plaster City, CA. Great to get some real testing time in it - because the next stop in my Baja 1000 prep is next week: the “Vegas to Reno” race! Photo: @ashthorp. #WhoopocalypseNow #TrophyTruck

node.text: Same rally test stage, but two VERY different vehicles. Directly compare these onboard videos of an AWD Subaru STI rally car -VS- a RWD Trophy Truck. The truck has 3x the power but more than 2x the weight. This is my kind of science! #WhoopocalypseNow #SubaruSTI #TrophyTruck

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ken Block on August 06, 2021. May be an image of car and road.

node.text: Things got real interesting when I raced the new Trophy Truck at Team O’Neils against my Subaru STI race car… in the STI’s natural habitat! The Trophy Truck is so big that I wasn’t sure if it would even be able to fit it in some of the tight and narrow turns the Team O’Neil stages have. Click the link (in bio) to see the ridiculous footage of that thing getting thrown around. #WhoopocalypseNow #SubaruSTI #TrophyTruck

node.text: I like jumps. And rally cars and Trophy Trucks are made to jump. And jump really well! Click the link in my bio to see them go head-to-head around a rally stage. #WhoopocalypseNow #SubaruSTI #TrophyTruck

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ken Block on August 05, 2021 tagging @alexgelsomino. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'MONSTER ARA 43 [HOONIGAN] VS Papas Beer [HOONIGAN] SR2 TOVO TIRES'.

node.text: Got droop?? Rally cars have a lot, but that Trophy Truck makes the rally car’s droop look not quite as impressive. Both can shred the gravel quite fast, so check out the new episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) to see a speed comparison test on a rally stage. #maddroop #SubaruSTI #TrophyTruck #WhoopocalypseNow

node.text: Trophy Truck VS rally car. On a jump! Both are built to jump, and both do it very well. But, how do they compare speed-wise on a rally stage?? Find out in the new episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio). #WhoopocalypseNow #TrophyTruck #SubaruSTI

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ken Block on August 05, 2021 tagging @geiserbros. May be an image of 2 people and outdoors.

node.text: Trophy Truck VS rally car. 6000lbs VS 3000lbs. But, with matching 2021 Hoonigan Racing livery by @itsaliving. Which did my co-driver @alexgelsomino prefer racing in?? (I think the one with the windscreen) See them both rip through a forest stage in the new episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio). #WhoopocalypseNow #TrophyTruck #SubaruSTI

node.text: The design that goes into building an 1,100 hp V8 beast like this Trophy Truck (by @geiserbros) is really amazing! And, one of the rad parts about working with render-whiz @ashthorp, is that he creates a detailed piece of digital work that we are able to build amazing visual content with it like this. But, what is even cooler is hopping into the belly of that beast and doing a little gravel slaying “science”! *More on that tomorrow on my YouTube channel! #TrophyTruck
